{"questionId":"25825","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>attempt to interchange <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>M1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; (accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>)<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25825","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ1.8b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find f-1x.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Composite functions, identity, finding inverse"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}